We use YAGSL for our swerve drive and it publishes odometry to Shuffleboard. There is a display of the game field that shows where the robot moves during auto and the teleop.

I think is is called shuffleboard. But it might by SmartDashboard. I can never remember the difference.

  1. click the 3 horizontal lines in the upper right corner
  2. go to settings then app settings
  3. set the robot IP in the provided box
  4. connect your computer to the robot via ethernet or wifi
  5. click again the 3 horizontal lines in the upper right corner
  6. click on telemetry
